cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is primarily focused on information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques for query expansion. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper uses clustering techniques to group similar words, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning and could be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses word vectors, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves computational complexity and optimization, which could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
